Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1606203994 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo Radio Carve </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Chamber of Deputies finally approved the 
constitutional reform bill this evening. The Chamber of Deputies 
president released a note this afternoon explaining the reasons 
that prompted the drafting of the current text, which gave rise 
to some observations by the Colorada and Batlleist Union. The 
bill was carried by 78 votes to one--that of Helios Sarthou of 
the MPP [People's Participation Movement]. The electoral court 
will now make arrangements for the plebiscite. [passage omitted] 

