<H3> <TI>   Ibero-American Leaders Meet, View Summit Results </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ibero-American Leaders Meet, View Summit Results </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Castro: Asylum-Seekers Want To Emigrate </H4>

<F P=102> PA1606185494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1758 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1606185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 16 Jun (EFE) -- Cuban President 
Fidel Castro believes that the entrance of Cubans into embassies 
and consulates in Havana does not constitute "any type of 
political problem." 
  In statements to Radio Cadena Nacional (RCN), from Cartagena 
de Indias, where he attended the Fourth Ibero-American Summit of 
Chiefs of State and Government, Castro said "the principal cause 
is that the people want to emigrate." 
  Dozens of Cubans have entered the Belgian and German 
diplomatic and consular missions in the Cuban capital in the 
past few days requesting "political asylum." 
  "They do so," Castro told RCN, "to promote illegal 
departures 
from the country and to promote incidents in order to reap 
political dividends." He added that "in our country, whoever 
wants to leave can do so." 

</TEXT>

