<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Urges Cuban Modernization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Urges Cuban Modernization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1706135694 Asuncion NOTICIAS in Spanish 17 Jun 94 p 28 </F>
<F P=103> PY1706135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion NOTICIAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by unidentified special correspondents] </F>
  [Text] Cartagena de Indias, Colombia -- President Juan 
Carlos Wasmosy on 16 June expressed his desire that the changes 
in Cuba should emerge without any bloodshed. He expressed his 
hope that Fidel Castro, on his own initiative, will begin the 
modernization of the Cuban state. 
  "I hope that day is close, I hope Fidel Castro will 
personally begin this modernization, this change that the whole 
world is expecting in Cuba. Let the change be implemented 
slowly, without trauma and without bloodshed," Wasmosy said. 
  He indicated that when the changes happen, Paraguay will 
open 
its doors to the Cuban people as a whole because the Cuban 
people are dear to us all. He maintained that everything has 
been done to try to bring about more freedom, a greater opening 
in the Caribbean island. He expressed his sadness regarding the 
blockade that surrounds Cuba. "We have asked for a program of 
opening for the Cuban people," Wasmosy said. 

</TEXT>

