BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 18 Jun (AFP) -- Cuban police sources 
reported that at least eight of the 118 Cuban refugees who have 
been at the Belgian ambassador's residence in Havana since 18 
May left this afternoon. The same sources said that most of 
those who left were women and children. 
  Reporters near the residence verified that there was more 
movement than usual of diplomatic vehicles, but they were unable 
to determine the exact number of people leaving the residence. 
  Another 21 persons have taken refuge at the German Embassy 
,and eight are at the Chilean Consulate, both located in the 
same neighborhood of Miramar. These people hope to obtain 
political asylum abroad. 

</TEXT>

