  [Text] Havana, 19 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- The Cuban Foreign 
Ministry has announced that the government "categorically" 
confirmed today that it will deny all persons who have 
forcefully entered a diplomatic mission permission to leave the 
island. 
  A Foreign Ministry note published in the weekly JUVENTUD 
REBELDE reports that the refusal will be maintained "even if 
they leave the embassy. No exception will be made." 
  The note reported that on 28 May more than 100 people 
entered 
the residence of the Belgian ambassador, on 13 June, 20 people 
broke into the German Embassy compound in a vehicle, and on 15 
June, nine people entered the Chilean Consulate. 

