<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Land Grants for Coffee Production Considered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Land Grants for Coffee Production Considered </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1706004794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1706004794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] One hundred seventy state and self-employed workers 
as well as pensioners from Guisa Municipality have applied for 
land grants to begin producing coffee in the mountains of Granma 
Province. The need to increase coffee production, a source of 
hard currency for Cuba, as well as a way of repopulating the 
mountain region of Guisa, which has a shortage of workers, was 
stressed in a meeting with 18 of these applicants. 
  Agriculture Minister Alfredo Jordan Morales and Alfredo 
Enriquez Pina announced that these workers and their relatives 
add up to 472 people; they can tend an area of 387 caballerias 
for coffee production. Jordan added that this situation is 
under study to set up contracts and to grant the land to them, 
since in the mountain regions of the country, there are 
approximately 2,000 caballerias that the state cannot make 
productive because of labor force shortages. 
  Alfredo Enriquez Pina stated that everyone moving to the 
mountains, people with demonstrated revolutionary aptitudes, 
people able to make the land produce, people able to repopulate 
the mountains, and zealous guardians of the Revolution must be 
given incentives. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

