<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gold, Sulphur Plants Begin Operations 14 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gold, Sulphur Plants Begin Operations 14 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1706235694 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1706235694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Manolo Rodriguez Salas from Pinar del Rio for the </F>
"NTV newscast"] 
  [Text] In a dignified salute to 14 June, the date when two 
of the greatest men in our history were born, Antonio Maceo and 
Ernesto Che Guevara, the citizens of Pinar del Rio have obtained 
the first 100 grams of gold at the plant in Castellanos, Minas 
de Matahambre Municipality. The investment had been planned 
barely two years and four months ago. 
  Hundreds of workers, mostly members of the Celso Maraotolara 
Brigade, as well as engineers, project managers, and technicians 
from the Ministry of Basic Industry gave additional proof of our 
people's intelligence and capacity when they got the plant 
operating without foreign consultation. Also, this is a 
one-of-a-kind project in the country. The new plant is capable 
of delivering up to 500 kg of gold per year for seven or eight 
years; it is considered the most feasible of all the 
gold-producing plants in Cuba. 
  The sulphur plant was also reopened. This year, it has a 
pledge to deliver 32,000 tons of sulphuric acid, which is an 
essential product for the nickel industry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

