<H3> <TI>   Cruces Municipality Assemblies Conclude </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cruces Municipality Assemblies Conclude </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1706022394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1706022394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Exclusive" program] </F>
  [Text] The progress report assemblies of delegates to 
constituents concluded in the Cruces Municipality in Cienfuegos 
Province with the participation of over 20,000 voters, 85 
percent of the total. The 82 assemblies planned were held in 
this locality where 230 issues were debated, of which 212 
reached solutions or answers, while 15 are to be solved with the 
support of the people and 18 are to be worked out with 
provincial and municipal organizations. 
  Among the issues most debated during this process were the 
difficulties presented by water distribution, the quality of 
bread, garbage pick-up, and the state's distribution of food 
supplies. Cruces Municipality government leaders described the 
progress reports assemblies as positive, where each assembly was 
a neighborhood party. The peoples' council of (Isla de Pino-La 
Trocha) was the most outstanding of the seven in the locality. 

