<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujimori on Arrest of `Very Important' SL Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujimori on Arrest of `Very Important' SL Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1806124794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0418 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1806124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 17 Jun (EFE) -- Peruvian President Alberto 
Fujimori announced today the arrest of a "very important" leader 
of the Shining Path [SL] terrorist group, whom he identified as 
Moises Simon Limaco Huayuscachi. Fujimori said that Limaco 
Huayuscachi was coordinator of the Shining Path's Central 
Directorate and was regarded as "the right arm" of Oscar Alberto 
Ramirez Durand, alias "Feliciano," currently the top leader of 
the Maoist group. 
  The Peruvian president said that Mario Vasquez, known as 
"Comrade Roberto," another ranking leader of the subversive 
organization, was also arrested. He is the one who occupied the 
post of Martha Huatay, who was in charge of the SL's "People's 
Aid" organization. 
  Huatay, one of the main terrorist leaders surrounding 
Abimael 
Guzman, the group's founder, ideologue, and foremost leader, was 
captured shortly after Guzman, who was arrested by policemen on 
12 September 1992. 
  Fujimori told newsmen that both terrorists were captured 
today in Comas district in the northern sector of Lima. He added 
that Limaco Huayuscachi was responsible for logistical support 
for "Feliciano" and said that his capture "will further weaken" 
the Shining Path organization, whose members have rejected the 
peace proposals made by Guzman to the Fujimori government and 
have chosen to pursue the path of violence. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

