<F P=102>   PA2006042894 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 2200 GMT 
19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2006042894 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] As soon as the public debt bonds are placed on the 
market, Fogade [Deposit Guarantee and Banking Protection Fund] 
will be able to return to the Central Bank of Venezuela [BCV] 
the funds this bank has disbursed to assist those banks that 
have been intervened. 
  BCV President Antonio Casas Gonzalez is reluctant to 
disburse 
additional funds, but he said there is no other option. 
  The public credit law, which aims to provide funds to 
Fogade, 
stipulates these bonds should not accrue interest and are 
nonnegotiable, but they may be redeemed early. 

</TEXT>

