17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1706174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Venezuelan Credit Bank has requested its 
withdrawal from the National Banking Association because it does 
not agree with statements issued by its official spokespersons. 
This was announced by Venezuelan Credit Bank President Garcia 
Mendoza, who described the National Banking Association's 
communique on the way in which the Executive Branch has handled 
the financial crisis as disrespectful. 
  Mendoza also did not agree with what National Banking 
Association President Jose Bouza Izquierdo said, because 
criticism is not among the duties of that association. Mendoza 
also said that he does not understand how the National Banking 
Association claims it works on behalf of the depositors during 
financial crises because the bankers acted contrary to this. 

