<H3> <TI>   Meets With Cabinet on Chiapas Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With Cabinet on Chiapas Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1806190694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1806190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Marcela Gutierrez from the "ACIR Radio News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] President Carlos Salinas met with members of his 
cabinet on 17 June. It has been reported that the central 
subject of the meeting was Chiapas. Shortly thereafter, the 
president of the republic announced the appointment of Hector 
Hernandez Llamas as executive spokesman for the peace process in 
Chiapas. Hernandez will work to fulfill the social and economic 
pledges made during the San Cristobal de las Casas talks. 
  There was much activity today at Los Pinos. Governor of 
Chiapas Javier Lopez Moreno arrived at 1400 local time. Agrarian 
Reform Secretary Victor Cervera Pacheco, Agriculture Secretary 
Carlos Hank Gonzalez, Communications and Transportation 
Secretary Emilio Gamboa Patron, and Chamber of Deputies leader 
Maria de los Angeles Moreno also attended the meeting. 
  At 1600 local time today, the Presidency's social 
Communications Directorate reported that Hernandez Llamas will 
act as intermediary between the federal government and the State 
of Chiapas. The office also said that Chiapas Governor Moreno 
will be in charge of peace process activities. Hernandez Llamas 
will work closely with Moreno. Moreno has held several public 
posts in the government. 

</TEXT>

