<F P=102>   PA1806190194 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1806190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Samuel Ruiz, bishop of San Cristobal de las Casas, 
has issued a communique endorsing the efforts that Manuel 
Camacho Solis carried out for five months and six days in favor 
of peace in Chiapas. 
  President of International Consultants Julio A. Millan 
thinks 
the country's economy should not be affected by Camacho Solis' 
resignation. 
  [Begin Millan recording] There are no losers. The people are 
not affected. In addition, all of the candidates still have 
freedom of movement. A citizen has resigned from a post, and 
this is similar to the resignation of any other official. The 
important thing now is to limit to the Chiapas area the causes 
and activities related to the problem. [end recording] 
  Felipe Solis, Federal Electoral Institute executive 
director, says there is no reason for Camacho Solis' resignation 
to affect the 21 August elections. 

</TEXT>

