<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] PAN [National Action Party] Mexican presidential 
candidate Diego Fernandez de Cevallos commented briefly on 
Manuel Camacho Solis' resignation from the post of commissioner 
for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas. Fernandez de Cevallos 
characterized the decision as very respectable, adding that the 
text of the resignation is serious and dignified. 
  Meanwhile, the Party of the Democratic Revolution in the 
Federal District said the resignation proves that there is a 
crisis within the PRI [Institutional Revolutionary Party]. 
  Deputy Rene Bejarano said Camacho's resignation proves that 
he is in disagreement with those who want to reduce democratic 
demands to the simplest expression. He warned that Camacho 
Solis' resignation increases the likelihood of renewed 
hostilities in Chiapas at any time. 

