<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   PGR Statement on Alleged Kidnapping by DEA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PGR Statement on Alleged Kidnapping by DEA </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1706164194 Mexico City EL FINANCIERO in Spanish 16 Jun 94 
p 42 </F>

<F P=103> PA1706164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City EL FINANCIERO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Attorney General's Office [PGR] has provided an 
explanation of the allegations, which have appeared in diverse 
national media, that in Ojinaga, Chihuahua, DEA agents kidnapped 
Modesto Lujan Valladares, who was taken to a penitentiary in 
Marfa, Texas. 
  1. No official of this institution has stated that DEA 
agents engaged in the alleged kidnapping of Lujan Valladares in 
Mexican territory, thereby violating national sovereignty. 
  2. It has been learned that Modesto Lujan Valladares was 
arrested on 21 April in Marfa, Texas, near the town of Presidio, 
which borders Ojinaga, Chihuahua. Lujan Valladares was found in 
a vehicle with Victor Valle Lujan, Isidro Armendariz Morales, 
and Samuel Garcia Wilfar, ready to sell 125 pounds of marijuana 
to an undercover agent. 
  3. Nevertheless, the PGR has initiated an investigation into 
the affair, instructing its representatives in the United States 
to obtain detailed information on the case to totally clear up 
the facts for the public. 
<H5>  Regarding Sovereignty </H5>
  Unrestricted respect for sovereignty in our nation and the 
decided struggle against international crime constitute an 
irrevocable commitment, which the PGR reaffirms to guarantee the 
community's security. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

