<F P=102>   FL1706211594 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1706211594 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 16 June, employees of the U.S. Embassy in 
Port-au-Prince began leaving Haiti for the United States. A 
preliminary group of seven people departed on a commercial 
American Airlines flight. Ambassador Swing took leave of this 
group at the airport in the presence of American journalists 
currently in Port-au-Prince. 
  It should be noted that about 70 members of the families of 
the U.S. diplomatic staff accredited in Haiti, including the 
spouse of Ambassador Swing, are due to leave Haiti before the 
suspension of commercial flights between Haiti and the United 
States on 25 June, and according to information provided by AFP, 
75 diplomats, including Ambassador Swing, will remain in 
Port-au- Prince. 
  It should also be pointed out that U.S. citizens residing in 
Haiti have begun to leave the country under their government's 
recommendation. 

</TEXT>

