<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry `Surprised' at Brazil Canceling Cavallo Trip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry `Surprised' at Brazil Canceling Cavallo Trip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY1806033194 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2250 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1806033194 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 17 Jun (NA) -- Economy Ministry 
sources said today that the Economy Ministry will not respond to 
the Brazilian Foreign Ministry's abrupt decision to suspend 
Domingo Cavallo's trip scheduled for the end of June. The 
suspension is presumably due to Brazilian annoyance over 
Argentina's support for Mexican President Carlos Salinas de 
Gortari to preside over the GATT general directorate. 
  The unexpected situation surprised the Economy Ministry, but 
the economic team decided not to comment until the situation 
clears up because there are still some conflicting reports on 
the issue. 
  The abrupt cancellation of Cavallo's visit to Brasilia was 
understood as a reprisal because Argentina gave its support to 
Salinas de Gortari instead of supporting Brazilian Economy 
Minister Rubens Ricupero from Rio de Janeiro to preside over the 
GATT directorate. 
  Argentina's support for the Mexican president was made 
public 
by President Carlos Menem during the Ibero-American summit this 
week. 
  The Brazilian press today published the remarks of several 
diplomats saying that the Brazilian Government felt 
"disappointed" at Menem's position, taking into account that 
Argentina is Brazil's partner in Mercosur [Common Market of the 
South] and it knew Brazil had proposed Ricupero for the post. 
  The diplomats also were annoyed because Brazil's seat was 
empty when Menem made the announcement. At the time, the 
Brazilian delegation was accompanying President Itamar Franco, 
who was mourning the sudden death of his nephew and private 
secretary. 
  The Brazilian Foreign Ministry lowered the tone after the 
dust raised by the affair settled and justified the suspension 
of Cavallo's visit by saying it was due to an "incompatibility 
in the agenda." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-34452 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat118bb_94001" </HT>


