<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   ELN Frees Kidnapped Electoral Members, Delegates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ELN Frees Kidnapped Electoral Members, Delegates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2106131894 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1200 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2106131894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From "Caracol's 0600 to 0900" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Six electoral members and two delegates of the Civil 
Registry office, who were kidnapped in El Cerrito, Santander 
Department, arrived in the outskirts of El Cerrito after walking 
on uneven terrain for hours. Marta Vera, Mario Salinas 
Antolines, Edgar Rodriguez Cruz, Amanda Mogollon, Luis Antonio 
Cuadros, and Jesus Alberto Campos, as well as Civil Registry 
delegates Flor Maria Rangel and Maria Pena were released after 
the 19 June elections. Upon arrival, they said they were treated 
well by members of the Efrain Pabon Pabon Front of the 
self-styled ELN [Army of National Liberation] who kidnapped them. 

</TEXT>

