  [Text] Havana, 19 Jun (PL) -- Another three illegal 
occupants of the residence of the Belgian ambassador in this 
capital voluntarily left the building this morning. 
  Police sources have confirmed this information. Now the 
number of people who have changed their mind and left the 
building in recent hours has climbed to 11. Seven persons have 
left in the past few days. According to local observers, this 
indicates that the idea that violent actions are useless is 
beginning to take hold among the group that forcefully entered 
the building on 28 May. 
  The Cuban Foreign Ministry today confirmed that whoever uses 
force to enter a diplomatic or consular installation in the 
country will lose the right to secure a visa to leave the 
country, even if they later leave the occupied diplomatic 
installation. 

