BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 16 Jun (PL) -- Mozambican National Assembly 
President Marcelino Dos Santos expressed here his government's 
and people's gratitude to Cuba for its contributions to his 
country's independence struggle. 
  During a meeting with Cuban internationalists who fought in 
Mozambique and on the occasion of the 19th anniversary of its 
independence from Portugal (25 June) Dos Santos recognized the 
help they received from Cuba during and after the armed struggle 
to consolidate and stabilize that nation. 
