<H3> <TI>   Sansaricq Guarantees Safety for Foreigners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sansaricq Guarantees Safety for Foreigners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2006193694 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2006193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bernard Sansaricq, president of the branch of the 
Senate controlled by the Alliance for Parliamentary Cohesion, 
has called on Haitian authorities to guarantee the safety of 
foreign nationals living on Haitian territory to avoid any 
pretext for military intervention by the international 
community. Sansaricq has asserted that the Senate will take all 
necessary measures to manage the situation. 
  [Begin recording, in Creole] [Sansaricq] Personally, I 
guarantee the international community that the Senate of the 
Republic will do its best to protect the safety and lives 
[pauses] so no attacks are perpetrated against foreigners in 
Haiti because what they want to show is that we are a band of 
wild people who cannot lead our country. 
  [Unidentified journalist] So you think that the 
international 
community has put economic diplomatic pressure on us, but that 
the threat of military intervention is not certain, contrary to 
what is being said? 
  [Sansaricq] There is no reason to invade Haiti because we 
are 
a peaceful country. If President Clinton takes upon himself the 
responsibility for putting a half-crazy man back in power -- a 
pro-Libyan, pro-Castroist, a man who could have established 
democracy in Haiti but did not -- I think President Clinton will 
regret it because he will have many problems, not in Haiti, but 
in the United States, with his own people, 65 percent of whom 
tell him no, do not enter Haiti. 
  We will do our best to manage the situation. If the 
intervention comes, we can do nothing about that. We will manage 
it the way it comes. We can do nothing about it, but we always 
[pauses] we would not like our country to be invaded. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

