<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attorney General's Office Reports Election-Related Crimes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attorney General's Office Reports Election-Related Crimes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2006051794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0130 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2006051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Julio de la Rue from the "TV Today" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Attorney General's Office has reported a slight 
increase in the number of reported election related crimes 
throughout the country compared to those filed during the first 
round. The report states there were claims of attempts to buy 
votes in five departments. Twenty people are under arrest, and 
they reportedly received gifts or favors to change their votes, 
according to the Attorney General's Office. 
  [Begin Attorney General Carlos Gustavo Arrieta recording] We 
received reports in certain instances that gifts such as lunch 
and tickets were given to people who voted. [end recording] 
  There was a positive assessment of the participation of 
state 
officials in the political campaign. 
  [Begin Arrieta recording] Quite the contrary, concerning 
officials' participation in the electoral process, there was a 
significant decrease. [end recording] 
  The Attorney General's Office will present to the judicial 
authorities the results of this report to allow them to conduct 
the appropriate investigations. 

</TEXT>

