<F P=102>   PA2206045694 Paris AFP in Spanish 0407 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2206045694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Port-au-Prince, 21 Jun (AFP) -- Tuesday night, the 
Ministry of Information, Coordination, and Culture announced 
that hereafter foreign journalists must "request and obtain" 
from that Ministry authorization to go to the cities in the 
provinces. 
  The objective of the measure is "to guarantee the security 
of 
foreign journalists in the country," the communique notes. Many 
foreign journalists, including the crews of the principal U.S. 
television stations, are in Port-au-Prince just as the new U.S. 
sanctions are to be enforced. 

</TEXT>

