<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on Inability To Accept Haitians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry on Inability To Accept Haitians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2106200994 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1757 GMT 21 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2106200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Panama City, 21 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- Panama has informed 
the United States that it is impossible for Panama to receive 
Haitian refugees because of the serious economic crisis the 
nation is experiencing, the Foreign Ministry reported here today. 
  Acting Foreign Minister Carlos Cordero said: "We have 
cooperated and will continue offering aid to the Haitians, but 
at this time it is impossible to receive them." After noting 
Panama's current high unemployment rate (15 percent), Cordero 
said a mass influx of Caribbean refugees would only worsen the 
Panamanian people's economic and social situation. 
  Last week the Panamanian Government denied press reports 
announcing the arrival of refugees in Panama. Recently, 
President William Clinton suggested to the nations of the region 
that they receive Haitian citizens who are fleeing the island 
because of the serious political crisis that threatens to end in 
a U.S. military invasion. 

</TEXT>

