<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alleged Shining Path Terrorist Released </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alleged Shining Path Terrorist Released </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2106215194 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1634 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2106215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 19 Jun (NA) -- Peruvian citizen Jorge 
Diaz Reategui, who was detained a week ago in the city of 
Tucuman on charges of being a member of the Shining Path [SL] 
guerrilla group, was released after it was confirmed that he is 
no longer a SL member. 
  Diaz Reategui was released on 17 June after an Interpol 
report confirmed that Diaz Reategui is a SL deserter who 
received special OAS political asylum. 
  The Peruvian police have confirmed that no arrest warrant 
has 
been issued on Diaz Reategui. It was also confirmed that his 
Argentine residence permit is authentic. 
  Diaz Reategui was detained at a hotel in the poor district 
of 
"El Bajo," near the bus terminal of the city of San Miguel de 
Tucuman. At the time of Diaz Reategui's detention, it was 
reported that he was participating in a meeting with other 
alleged guerrillas who escaped. 
  Interior Minister Carlos Ruckauf accused Diaz Reategui of 
participating in protests in some northern provinces. Ruckauf 
noted that those who were meeting with Diaz Reategui "had been 
spotted in other parts of our country, participating in public 
disorders." 

</TEXT>

